<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06298228 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06298228 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  Standard Products Co., a Cleveland maker of automobile trim and door andwindow seals, named Theodore K. Zampetis president and chief operatingofficer.;   Zampetis filled a vacancy created in June, when Robert B. Stevenswas appointed senior vice president to run the military division, a unit thatthe company has since decided to close.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  STANDARD PRODUCTS APPOINTS PRESIDENT  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Zampetis, 46, has engineered several turnarounds and consolidations inrecent years at Standard Products divisions in Canada, Britain and the UnitedStates.;   In one case, for example, he was called in to solve costly qualityand training problems at the company's plants in Britain, which make trim andseals for the Ford Motor Co. In his new role, Zampetis said he hoped to beable to head off any problems before they arise.;   Zampetis' appointmentfollows the company's report that it had returned to profitability in the mostrecent quarter after four consecutive periods of losses.;   The bulk of thecompany's $592 million in annual revenues last year was derived from sales ofautomobile-related products, including body trim. The company also makes sealsfor refrigerators, and it operates a truck-tire retreading operation.;  Zampetis, a native of Greece who is now an American citizen, graduated fromthe Greek Merchant Marine Academy in 1964 with a bachelor's degree inelectromechanical engineering.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  New York Times  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Home  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911024  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  October  </MONTH><PG.COL>  6G  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  215  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday, October 24, 199100298228,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  <